#(3) 10[5]
head(lvr_prices,10)
#(4) 
#  1. city_land_type
#  2. total_price > 0
#  3. building_sqmeter > 0
#  4. finish_ymd 
#  ,house[8]
house = lvr_prices[lvr_prices$city_land_type == '' & lvr_prices$total_price > 0 & lvr_prices$building_sqmeter > 0 & lvr_prices$finish_ymd != '',]
#(5) house(total_price)(building_sqmeter)
#    (price_per_sqmeter)[5]
house$price_per_sqmeter = round(house$total_price / house$building_sqmeter)
#(6) housescale() (price_per_sqmeter)
#    outlier(z-score > 3)[5]
house = house[abs(scale(house$price_per_sqmeter)) <= 3,]
#(7) house(area)? ? [5]

#(10) (finish_ymd)(building_age)house
#hint1:  Sys.Date()
#hint2: 365
#hint3: (integer) [8]
house$finish_ymd = as.Date(house$finish_ymd)
house$building_age = round( (Sys.Date() - house$finish_ymd ) / 365)
#(11) finalhouse_danger
#     househouse_dangerleft outer joinjoin
#     house [5]
load('~/lecture/riii/final/house_danger.RData')
house = merge(house,house_danger,by = 'ID', all.x = T)
#(12) house8:2
#     trainsettestset [5]
set.seed(1206)
ind<-sample(1:2, size=nrow(house), replace=T, prob=c(0.8, 0.2))
trainset=house[ind==1,]
testset=house[ind==2,]
#(13) rpart(danger)
#     (area), (building_age), (building_sqmeter),
#     (building_type)(price_per_sqmeter)
#     5house.rp [5]
library('rpart')
house.rp<-rpart(danger ~ area+building_age+building_type+building_sqmeter+price_per_sqmeter, data=trainset)
#(14) plot()text()house.rp [5]

plot(house.rp, uniform=TRUE,branch = 0.6, margin=0.1)
text(house.rp, cex=0.7)

#(15) (prune)house.rp [5]
house.rp$cptable
##           CP nsplit rel error    xerror        xstd
## 1 0.19922074      0 1.0000000 1.0000000 0.011977156
## 2 0.09181772      2 0.6015585 0.6015585 0.009618499
## 3 0.06522107      4 0.4179231 0.4180925 0.008141897
## 4 0.02498729      5 0.3527020 0.3530408 0.007521454
## 5 0.01000000      8 0.2746061 0.2751143 0.006681431
house.cp = house.rp$cptable[which.min(house.rp$cptable[,"xerror"]), "CP"]
house.rp=prune(house.rp, cp=house.cp)
#(16) (testset)accuracy, precision, recall [5]

predictions =predict(house.rp, testset,type = 'class')
library('caret')

library('e1071')

library(ROCR)

predictions <-predict(house.rp, testset, type="prob")
pred.to.roc<-predictions[, 'YES']
pred.rocr<-prediction(pred.to.roc, testset$danger)
perf.tpr.rocr<-performance(pred.rocr, "tpr","fpr")
plot(perf.tpr.rocr)

perf.rocr<-performance(pred.rocr, measure ="auc", x.measure="cutoff")
print(perf.rocr@y.values)
